						<div class="postbody">I would imagine that even if this worked, if mode 7 was on the right side of the screen (or just anywhere that's not the leftmost side) it's very likely that the deformation computations would be completely wrong since they weren't started at the left side of the screen. Or does the hardware compute it regardless of which mode is currently being displayed?<br /><br />I would imagine this could screw up other modes as well in similar ways (e.g. tiles not being fetched correctly at the transition area, scrolling being broken, etc. - depends on how the hardware implements this).</div>

