				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It depends on how big the &quot;mode-7&quot; layer is, if it is scaling, rotation or both, and if it's a full 360 degree rotation, or just tilting.  If it's small sprites, it could pre-rotate sprite frames in wram while the game is running, so it can smoothly rotate several sprites by the time they appear onscreen.  Same for scaling, but both at the same time would eat up a lot of wram.  If it is a larger object, that is 128x128 or 256x256, it can be smoothly tilted back and forth using MODE-2 offset-per-tile mode, and HDMA line-scrolling.  You can use tilting to transition between large rotation steps, to make a full 360 degree.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

